<subSubSection pageId="100" pageNumber="101" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="100.[151,1437,598,1404]" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1272,1297]" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">Etymology:</emphasis>
This name refers to the medially bowed male cerci (Latin ‘cercus’: tail, small appendage at the end of the abdomen; Latin ‘arcuatus’: bent like a bow).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
